                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@Thrustmaster: It really wouldn&apos;t. Serving different JS to different browsers means you have to add &lt;code&gt;Vary: User-Agent&lt;/code&gt; to your response, otherwise caching proxies will store one version and send it to the other kind of browser. But &lt;code&gt;Vary: User-Agent&lt;/code&gt; makes the response uncachable in IE.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
