                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@sskular that was a very good question---thanks. I tested it for us, as I have a Lenovo X1 Yoga available with Win10. 1) &lt;code&gt;localStorage.mobile&lt;/code&gt; is &lt;code&gt;undefined&lt;/code&gt; no matter what. 2) When the laptop is in keyboard mode, &lt;code&gt;window.navigator.maxTouchPoints&lt;/code&gt; is &lt;code&gt;1&lt;/code&gt;; so isMobile was &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt;. 3) When the keyboard is flipped back and the laptop is in tablet mode, &lt;code&gt;window.navigator.maxTouchPoints&lt;/code&gt; is &lt;code&gt;10&lt;/code&gt;; so isMobile was &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt;. Now the subjective question: Do we consider a tablet or laptop in tablet-mode as mobile? &lt;/span&gt;

